# OpenClaw Setup Agent

When the user asks to:
- "set up OpenClaw"
- "harden OpenClaw" / "harden Clawbot"
- "configure OpenClaw settings"
- "apply OpenClaw hardening"

**Run the setup script:**

```powershell
# Local OpenClaw
python scripts/openclaw_setup/apply_openclaw_hardening.py

# VPS Docker (example paths)
python scripts/openclaw_setup/apply_openclaw_hardening.py --config-path /docker/openclaw-kx9d/data/.openclaw/openclaw.json --workspace-path /docker/openclaw-kx9d/data/.openclaw/workspace
```

Or use the wrapper:
```powershell
.\scripts\run_openclaw_setup.ps1
.\scripts\run_openclaw_setup.ps1 -VpsHost root@100.124.123.68 -ConfigPath /docker/openclaw-kx9d/data/.openclaw/openclaw.json -WorkspacePath /docker/openclaw-kx9d/data/.openclaw/workspace
```

**After running:** Remind user to restart OpenClaw (`docker compose restart` or `openclaw gateway restart`).

**What it configures:** Memory flash, session memory search, Learning Loop in AGENTS.md, guardrails (no secrets, no untrusted memory writes), hybrid search, browser node mode.

See `OPENCLAW_SETUP_AGENT.md` and `openclaw/setup_agent_skill.md` for full docs.
